like Sweat with Kayla, and Lyft,
and they are lightning fast too.

00:15:03.568 --> 00:15:06.204 line:92%
Let's take a look.

00:15:06.204 --> 00:15:10.508 line:92%
With one tap, I can call a car.

00:15:10.508 --> 00:15:11.710 line:92%
Yikes, three minutes.

00:15:11.710 --> 00:15:15.613
I have so much to show you
like New Apps, Reminders

00:15:15.613 --> 00:15:19.718
and Find My Friends that have
been designed specifically

00:15:19.718 --> 00:15:21.119
for this kind of
quick interaction.

00:15:21.119 --> 00:15:22.921 line:92%
Let's look at Reminders.

00:15:22.921 --> 00:15:25.523
Now, I can keep all my lists
with me throughout the day

00:15:25.523 --> 00:15:28.727
and just check things
off as I get them done.

00:15:28.727 --> 00:15:30.862 line:92%
Here's my bucket list.

00:15:30.862 --> 00:15:33.064
You don't get to
do this very often

00:15:33.064 --> 00:15:35.500
but today is just
one of those days.

00:15:35.500 --> 00:15:44.576 line:92%
[ Cheering and Applause ]

00:15:46.344 --> 00:15:48.847
Find My Friends takes
advantage of background updates

00:15:48.847 --> 00:15:51.816
to ensure I always have the
latest and greatest location

00:15:51.816 --> 00:15:53.385 line:92%
for my friends and family.

00:15:53.385 --> 00:15:55.186
Now, I never have to worry
about whether my kids got

00:15:55.186 --> 00:15:58.156 line:92%
to their activities on time.

00:15:58.156 --> 00:16:01.326
And we wanted to make changing
your watch face as easy

00:16:01.326 --> 00:16:03.361
as swiping through
apps on your dock.

00:16:03.361 --> 00:16:05.797
And while Minnie is fabulous
for a casual weekend,

00:16:05.797 --> 00:16:08.533
sometimes I want to wear
something simple and elegant.

00:16:08.533 --> 00:16:11.770
Now, with an edge-to-edge swipe,
I can get to my Numerals face.

00:16:11.770 --> 00:16:16.007
And for those of you as obsessed
with closing your rings as I am,

00:16:16.007 --> 00:16:18.410 line:92%
we now have the Activity face.

00:16:18.410 --> 00:16:19.844 line:92%
Every time I raise my wrist,

00:16:19.844 --> 00:16:22.080
I get to see those big
beautiful rings reminding me

00:16:22.080 --> 00:16:23.615 line:92%
to get up and get moving.

00:16:23.615 --> 00:16:27.819
And I can launch my
workout right from the face.

00:16:27.819 --> 00:16:30.155
With the New Quick Start
feature, I can bypass setting

00:16:30.155 --> 00:16:33.491 line:92%
up a goal and just get started.

00:16:33.491 --> 00:16:36.594 line:92%
[ Beeping Sound ]

00:16:36.594 --> 00:16:40.331
I didn't really come dressed for
a workout today, so I'm going

00:16:40.331 --> 00:16:44.369
to swipe over and that then
take us back to our watch face.

00:16:44.369 --> 00:16:46.838
Notifications are still right
where you think they'd be,

00:16:46.838 --> 00:16:49.074
pulled down from the
top of the screen.

00:16:49.074 --> 00:16:51.910
This is a message I saved
from my friend Isabel.

00:16:51.910 --> 00:16:54.679
She's been teaching me a little
Mandarin and she wants me

00:16:54.679 --> 00:16:56.881
to reply about dinner
tonight in Chinese.

00:16:56.881 --> 00:17:00.585
I can do that with the
new Scribble feature.

00:17:00.585 --> 00:17:02.687
Scribble works in
English and Chinese

00:17:02.687 --> 00:17:05.323
and it knows what language
my keyboard has been set to.

00:17:05.323 --> 00:17:09.461
So with my finger, I can
write out a quick message.

00:17:09.461 --> 00:17:18.536 line:92%
[ Cheering and Applause ]

00:17:20.305 --> 00:17:23.842 line:92%
[Foreign language] or 8 o'clock.

00:17:23.842 --> 00:17:26.344
Those are just a few of
the features of watchOS 3

00:17:26.344 --> 00:17:27.512 line:92%
but of course there's more.

00:17:27.512 --> 00:17:29.481 line:92%
Back to Kevin.

00:17:29.481 --> 00:17:36.621 line:92%
[ Cheering and Applause ]

00:17:36.621 --> 00:17:37.555 line:92%
That was awesome, Stacey.

00:17:37.555 --> 00:17:38.690 line:92%
Thank you.

00:17:38.690 --> 00:17:40.258
And it's so exciting to
achieve this new level

00:17:40.258 --> 00:17:41.926 line:92%
of performance on the watch.

00:17:41.926 --> 00:17:43.161 line:92%
And we're finding that people

00:17:43.161 --> 00:17:45.530
who are wearing Apple
Watch wear it all the time.

00:17:45.530 --> 00:17:49.067
And this opens up some new
great ways that we can help.

00:17:49.067 --> 00:17:50.435
And one of these is
actually getting help

00:17:50.435 --> 00:17:52.036 line:92%
in critical situations just

00:17:52.036 --> 00:17:53.638
by pushing a button
that's actually on you.

00:17:53.638 --> 00:17:56.941
So you might be having a
medical emergency, for example,

00:17:56.941 --> 00:17:59.110 line:92%
or a safety situation.

00:17:59.110 --> 00:18:01.212
And we're going to be able
to help with that with SOS

00:18:01.212 --> 00:18:04.182
on the watch and we're going to
make it easy to call for help.

00:18:04.182 --> 00:18:07.018
To activate it, you just press
and hold the side button.

00:18:07.018 --> 00:18:09.721
It's going to countdown to
let you know it's calling 911.

00:18:09.721 --> 00:18:11.589
And then you're going
to be on a live call

00:18:11.589 --> 00:18:14.025
with the emergency services
right on your watch.

00:18:14.025 --> 00:18:17.328
This works either as a cellular
call via your iPhone or directly

00:18:17.328 --> 00:18:18.730
from the watch if
you're connected to WiFi.

00:18:18.730 --> 00:18:23.334
Now if you're done talking on
the phone's emergency services,

00:18:23.334 --> 00:18:26.304
the watch will automatically
notify your emergency contacts,

00:18:26.304 --> 00:18:27.705 line:92%
they'll send them a message.

00:18:27.705 --> 00:18:30.975
The message also will include
a map of your current location

00:18:30.975 --> 00:18:32.143 line:92%
so they know where you are

00:18:32.143 --> 00:18:34.245
and they can coordinate
with each other.

00:18:34.245 --> 00:18:35.847 line:92%
Now, after sending the message,

00:18:35.847 --> 00:18:38.283
your watch will actually
now show your medical ID

00:18:38.283 --> 00:18:40.885
which is also a new
feature in watchOS.

00:18:40.885 --> 00:18:43.555
It has things like for
example your age and allergies

00:18:43.555 --> 00:18:45.723
and other information
you'd like to put there.

00:18:45.723 --> 00:18:48.560
And SOS works not
only just in the US

00:18:48.560 --> 00:18:50.195 line:92%
but it works internationally.

00:18:50.195 --> 00:18:52.564
So for example you might
be traveling to some place

00:18:52.564 --> 00:18:55.667
like Hong Kong and you might not
know what the emergency number

00:18:55.667 --> 00:18:58.503
is to call but your
Apple Watch does.

00:18:58.503 --> 00:19:05.743 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:19:05.743 --> 00:19:08.980
So in this case, it calls
999 rather than 911.

00:19:08.980 --> 00:19:11.249
So this is an emergency
feature that isn't one

00:19:11.249 --> 00:19:13.151
that you'll use often
but when you need it,

00:19:13.151 --> 00:19:14.986
it's going to be
there and that's SOS.

00:19:14.986 --> 00:19:19.757
Now, one of the primary reasons
people are wearing the watch

00:19:19.757 --> 00:19:20.959 line:92%
today is for fitness and health.

00:19:20.959 --> 00:19:23.461
And we're enhancing the
activity and workout apps

00:19:23.461 --> 00:19:26.364
and we're adding a new app that
we think you're going to love.

00:19:26.364 --> 00:19:29.467
Take a look at this,
please welcome Jay Blahnik.

00:19:29.467 --> 00:19:32.270 line:92%
[ Cheering and Applause ]

00:19:32.270 --> 00:19:32.837 line:92%
&gt;&gt; Thanks, Kevin.

00:19:32.837 --> 00:19:34.272 line:92%
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:19:37.475 --> 00:19:39.811
&gt;&gt; So we know that one
of the most popular apps

00:19:39.811 --> 00:19:41.980
in the Apple Watch
is the Activity app.

00:19:41.980 --> 00:19:43.815
And as Kevin and
Stacey have mentioned,

00:19:43.815 --> 00:19:46.584
many people have told us that
they actually become more active

00:19:46.584 --> 00:19:49.988
because they become addicted
to closing the activity rings.

00:19:49.988 --> 00:19:51.189 line:92%
And we love hearing that.

00:19:51.189 --> 00:19:54.192
But we also know that
many people are motivated

00:19:54.192 --> 00:19:55.627 line:92%
by other things.

00:19:55.627 --> 00:19:57.562
Some people are motivated
by getting support

00:19:57.562 --> 00:19:59.130 line:92%
from their family and friends.

00:19:59.130 --> 00:20:01.199
And if you're like
me, you're motivated

00:20:01.199 --> 00:20:04.002
by good old fashion competition
and we wanted to make

00:20:04.002 --> 00:20:06.037 line:92%
that possible as well.

00:20:06.037 --> 00:20:10.241
So with watchOS, we're
introducing activity sharing.

00:20:10.241 --> 00:20:11.743 line:92%
And it couldn't be simpler.

00:20:11.743 --> 00:20:13.645
All you have to do
is swipe to the right

00:20:13.645 --> 00:20:15.480 line:92%
of your own activity rings

00:20:15.480 --> 00:20:17.382
and there you'll see
your selected family

00:20:17.382 --> 00:20:18.750 line:92%
and friend's rings as well.

00:20:18.750 --> 00:20:22.887
Now you can sort by whatever
metric is most important to you.

00:20:22.887 --> 00:20:25.990
So you can sort by steps,
you can sort by workouts,

00:20:25.990 --> 00:20:28.059
you can even sort
by exercise minutes.

00:20:28.059 --> 00:20:31.329
Here you'll see that I've sorted
by the move ring and I'm right

00:20:31.329 --> 00:20:32.730 line:92%
where you'd expect me to be.

00:20:32.730 --> 00:20:37.068
I'm getting by butt kicked by
Stacey but I'm annihilating Jeff

00:20:37.068 --> 00:20:40.204 line:92%
which makes me very happy.

00:20:40.204 --> 00:20:43.341
If you want to see more details,
all you do is tap on anyone

00:20:43.341 --> 00:20:46.077
on your activity list and
you'll get an up close look

00:20:46.077 --> 00:20:49.180
at their activity rings,
but you can also see things

00:20:49.180 --> 00:20:50.715 line:92%
like their daily step count

00:20:50.715 --> 00:20:54.485
and their workouts even
from third parties.

00:20:54.485 --> 00:20:56.888
But one of my favorite
features is

00:20:56.888 --> 00:20:58.956
that you can communicate
directly with the people

00:20:58.956 --> 00:21:00.758
that you're sharing
activity with right

00:21:00.758 --> 00:21:03.695
in the Activity app
through messages.

00:21:03.695 --> 00:21:06.731
And when you do, you'll get
smart replies that are geared

00:21:06.731 --> 00:21:08.966 line:92%
around fitness and activity.

00:21:08.966 --> 00:21:13.338
Some are supportive, some
are a little more competitive

00:21:13.338 --> 00:21:15.039
but you can also
do some fun things.

00:21:15.039 --> 00:21:16.641
For example, at the
end of a workout,

00:21:16.641 --> 00:21:18.209
you could send your
raising heart rate to one

00:21:18.209 --> 00:21:19.577 line:92%
of your activity friends.

00:21:19.577 --> 00:21:25.950
Or your raising heart rate to
one of your activity friends

00:21:25.950 --> 00:21:30.054
or you can also send smack
talk in your own voice right

00:21:30.054 --> 00:21:31.823 line:92%
through audio messages.

00:21:31.823 --> 00:21:33.624
So we think this is going
to be a great way for you

00:21:33.624 --> 00:21:35.493
and your friends
to stay motivated

00:21:35.493 --> 00:21:40.164
to keep each other active and
we can't wait for you to try it.

00:21:40.164 --> 00:21:43.267
Now, our team has been
working hard to enable features

00:21:43.267 --> 00:21:44.635 line:92%
that would allow more people

00:21:44.635 --> 00:21:47.205
to use the Activity
and Workout apps.

00:21:47.205 --> 00:21:48.673
And one group we've
been thinking a lot

00:21:48.673 --> 00:21:51.609 line:92%
about is wheelchair users.

00:21:51.609 --> 00:21:54.612
Now, many wheelchair users
already have an Apple Watch.

00:21:54.612 --> 00:21:57.115
And they've witnessed and
told us that they love it

00:21:57.115 --> 00:21:59.217
because it gives them
instant access to messages

00:21:59.217 --> 00:22:00.885
and notifications
right from their wrist.

00:22:00.885 --> 00:22:02.954
And this is particularly
important

00:22:02.954 --> 00:22:04.689
because many wheelchair
users have

00:22:04.689 --> 00:22:08.226
to tuck away their iPhone
securely throughout the day.

00:22:08.226 --> 00:22:11.062
But to do a great activity
and workout experience,

00:22:11.062 --> 00:22:13.531
we also recognize that we
couldn't just use the same

00:22:13.531 --> 00:22:15.933
algorithms that we've used
for non-wheelchair users

00:22:15.933 --> 00:22:19.303
because the biomechanics
are completely different.

00:22:19.303 --> 00:22:22.240
For example, many wheelchair
users use a semicircular

00:22:22.240 --> 00:22:24.208
technique when they're pushing
their wheelchair throughout

00:22:24.208 --> 00:22:25.543 line:92%
the day.

00:22:25.543 --> 00:22:28.679
But as the terrain changes
and the speed changes,

00:22:28.679 --> 00:22:30.615
they may switch to
an arc technique

00:22:30.615 --> 00:22:32.683 line:92%
or a single-loop over technique.

00:22:32.683 --> 00:22:34.285
And this is what
makes it complicated.

00:22:34.285 --> 00:22:37.321
These are only a few of the
techniques that they may use.

00:22:37.321 --> 00:22:40.558
We knew that to do this right,
we not only have to do a lot

00:22:40.558 --> 00:22:42.760
of studies but we
would also need

00:22:42.760 --> 00:22:45.029 line:92%
to enlist the help of experts.

00:22:45.029 --> 00:22:47.532
So, we worked with the
Challenged Athletes Foundation

00:22:47.532 --> 00:22:49.167 line:92%
and the Lakeshore Foundation.

00:22:49.167 --> 00:22:51.803
These are two of the
world's largest organizations

00:22:51.803 --> 00:22:54.038
that are dedicated to
promoting physical fitness

00:22:54.038 --> 00:22:56.140 line:92%
for people in wheelchairs.

00:22:56.140 --> 00:22:59.043
With their help, we were
able to conduct the studies.

00:22:59.043 --> 00:23:00.878
And we were able to do
it on a wide variety

00:23:00.878 --> 00:23:03.915
of wheelchair users
including some veterans.

00:23:03.915 --> 00:23:07.285
And now, wheelchair users
will have a setting.

00:23:07.285 --> 00:23:11.489
The time to stand notifications
will be changed to time to roll.

00:23:11.489 --> 00:23:17.829 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:23:17.829 --> 00:23:19.230 line:92%
There will be two workouts

00:23:19.230 --> 00:23:22.066
in the workout apps specifically
dedicated to wheelchair users

00:23:22.066 --> 00:23:24.836
and of course the activity
rings will be optimized

00:23:24.836 --> 00:23:26.704 line:92%
for wheelchair pushes.

00:23:26.704 --> 00:23:29.307
We could not be more
excited about this feature

00:23:29.307 --> 00:23:31.142
and we're incredibly
thankful to our partners

00:23:31.142 --> 00:23:33.511 line:92%
for helping make it possible.

00:23:33.511 --> 00:23:39.550 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:23:39.550 --> 00:23:41.552
Now, one of the things that
we've learned about health

00:23:41.552 --> 00:23:43.387
in Apple Watch is
that simple things

00:23:43.387 --> 00:23:45.890
like the activity rings
can be very powerful

00:23:45.890 --> 00:23:48.159
at helping people
change behavior.

00:23:48.159 --> 00:23:49.994
But we also know that
there's a lot more

00:23:49.994 --> 00:23:52.063 line:92%
to health than just fitness.

00:23:52.063 --> 00:23:54.732
And we've been thinking
way beyond that.

00:23:54.732 --> 00:23:57.869
So with watchOS, we're
launching a brand new app

00:23:57.869 --> 00:24:00.671 line:92%
for health, it's called Breathe.

00:24:00.671 --> 00:24:02.373 line:92%
And it's designed to guide you

00:24:02.373 --> 00:24:04.642
through simple deep
breathing sessions

00:24:04.642 --> 00:24:08.012
that can help you quiet
your mind, relax your body

00:24:08.012 --> 00:24:11.883
and just better deal
with everyday stress.

00:24:11.883 --> 00:24:14.952
Now, yoga practitioners have
been using deep breathing

00:24:14.952 --> 00:24:17.455
exercises for thousands
of years as a way

00:24:17.455 --> 00:24:19.957
to positively impact
the body and mind.

00:24:19.957 --> 00:24:22.960
But the medical community has
also embraced deep breathing

00:24:22.960 --> 00:24:25.429
as a great way to
improve daily health.

00:24:25.429 --> 00:24:28.666
Dr. Deepak Chopra, one
of the early advocates

00:24:28.666 --> 00:24:32.036
of body-mind medicine has said,
"Taking a moment every day

00:24:32.036 --> 00:24:34.672
to do some deep breathing
can reduce stress,

00:24:34.672 --> 00:24:36.340 line:92%
calm the body-mind as well

00:24:36.340 --> 00:24:38.576
as have a long term
health benefits."

00:24:38.576 --> 00:24:41.913
Now to get to the
app, it's easy.

00:24:41.913 --> 00:24:44.282
You can launch it from your
watch face, you can launch it

00:24:44.282 --> 00:24:48.452
from the dock or like
the stand reminders,

00:24:48.452 --> 00:24:51.556
you can actually set smart
notifications to remind you

00:24:51.556 --> 00:24:55.893
and start building this as
a habit every single day.

00:24:55.893 --> 00:24:58.896
When you open the app, you
can easily change the amount

00:24:58.896 --> 00:25:00.298
of time you want
to do your session,

00:25:00.298 --> 00:25:04.769
from one to five minutes just
by turning the digital crown.

00:25:04.769 --> 00:25:07.838
And when you're in the app
experience, you'll be guided

00:25:07.838 --> 00:25:11.208
by beautiful visuals that make
it really easy to follow along.

00:25:11.208 --> 00:25:14.045
And if you prefer to do
this with your eyes closed,

00:25:14.045 --> 00:25:16.047
you can turn on the
haptic feedback

00:25:16.047 --> 00:25:18.716 line:92%
and gentle taps will guide you

00:25:18.716 --> 00:25:21.118
and you can do without
even looking.

00:25:21.118 --> 00:25:23.821
When the session is over,
you'll get a summary.

00:25:23.821 --> 00:25:26.123
And you'll also get your heart
rate from the last few seconds

00:25:26.123 --> 00:25:28.225 line:92%
of the session you just did.

00:25:28.225 --> 00:25:30.428
Now if you already
do deep breathing,

00:25:30.428 --> 00:25:32.263
we think this is going to be
a great way for you to fit it

00:25:32.263 --> 00:25:33.965 line:92%
into your day more often.

00:25:33.965 --> 00:25:35.900
But for those of you that
don't, we think this is going

00:25:35.900 --> 00:25:38.970
to be a great way to get started
and just one more simple way

00:25:38.970 --> 00:25:41.372
that it can help you
live a better day.

00:25:41.372 --> 00:25:43.908
These are just a few of the
exciting updates we have planned

00:25:43.908 --> 00:25:45.509
for fitness and health
in watchOS.

00:25:45.509 --> 00:25:48.512
Now I'm going to give
it back to Kevin.

00:25:48.512 --> 00:25:55.319 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:25:55.319 --> 00:25:56.087 line:92%
&gt;&gt; Thank you, Jay.

00:25:56.087 --> 00:25:57.221 line:92%
That was really terrific.

00:25:57.221 --> 00:25:59.256
I was actually using the
Breathe app back stage.

00:25:59.256 --> 00:26:00.758 line:92%
It helped me a bit.

00:26:00.758 --> 00:26:07.431
So, watchOS 3 is a giant step
forward for you as developers.

00:26:07.431 --> 00:26:10.067
When someone adds your apps
to dock or to the watch face,

00:26:10.067 --> 00:26:12.370
it benefits from all the
instant launch experience

00:26:12.370 --> 00:26:14.405
that we're showing and
you get background time

00:26:14.405 --> 00:26:16.974
to update your information
before someone goes and looks.

00:26:16.974 --> 00:26:19.210
And that will enable
really quick interactions

00:26:19.210 --> 00:26:20.978 line:92%
with your app on the watch.

00:26:20.978 --> 00:26:23.214
Now you can already build
apps that are native to watch

00:26:23.214 --> 00:26:24.915
that you can run
independent of iPhone,

00:26:24.915 --> 00:26:26.517 line:92%
but we're also adding a number

00:26:26.517 --> 00:26:28.119
of new APIs you can
take advantage

00:26:28.119 --> 00:26:30.721
of when you're building
apps for the watch.

00:26:30.721 --> 00:26:33.591
One of those is support now
for Apple Pay within your app

00:26:33.591 --> 00:26:36.827
on the watch, so you can
