as well and have those
files be available to us

00:40:01.565 --> 00:40:03.834 line:92%
on the go on our iPhones.

00:40:03.834 --> 00:40:05.502 line:92%
Now you can.

00:40:05.502 --> 00:40:11.208 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:40:11.208 --> 00:40:13.577 line:92%
Next up, optimized storage.

00:40:13.577 --> 00:40:15.445 line:92%
You know, we love using our Macs

00:40:15.445 --> 00:40:16.947
and we fill them
with so much stuff.

00:40:16.947 --> 00:40:19.082
But you're going to end up
with a situation like this.

00:40:19.082 --> 00:40:22.385
And, we know, what
do you do about it?

00:40:22.385 --> 00:40:24.621
Well, it turns out we're
going to give you a solution.

00:40:24.621 --> 00:40:26.556 line:92%
And it works in two ways.

00:40:26.556 --> 00:40:30.160
First, it helps you make
room for the files that--

00:40:30.160 --> 00:40:33.830
your new files by keeping your
older ones up in the Cloud.

00:40:33.830 --> 00:40:36.433
So, whether it's your
full resolution photos,

00:40:36.433 --> 00:40:38.735
when your others are in
iCloud Drive or movies

00:40:38.735 --> 00:40:41.171
that you've already
watched in iTunes

00:40:41.171 --> 00:40:44.474
or even those old mail
attachments, we can clear off

00:40:44.474 --> 00:40:46.443
that space locally and
make those things available

00:40:46.443 --> 00:40:47.644 line:92%
to you on demand.

00:40:47.644 --> 00:40:49.846
But we also want to make
it easy for you to get rid

00:40:49.846 --> 00:40:52.949
of files you'll never
use again automatically.

00:40:52.949 --> 00:40:56.052
Things like your Safari web
cache and maybe the trash

00:40:56.052 --> 00:40:57.554
that you keep forgetting
to empty

00:40:57.554 --> 00:41:00.056
and redundant data that's stored
by mail, well, we can get rid

00:41:00.056 --> 00:41:01.658 line:92%
of all of that as well.

00:41:01.658 --> 00:41:04.294
And we provide a really
simple user interface

00:41:04.294 --> 00:41:05.929 line:92%
to help you do it.

00:41:05.929 --> 00:41:09.199
Now, as a task, we took a
system that was nearly full,

00:41:09.199 --> 00:41:11.468
had about let's say
20 gigs free,

00:41:11.468 --> 00:41:13.236 line:92%
and we put it through the paces.

00:41:13.236 --> 00:41:16.706
Now, it had a lot of photos
and a lot of documents.

00:41:16.706 --> 00:41:19.342
It had movies that were
already watched, mail with lots

00:41:19.342 --> 00:41:22.245
of attachment, apps,
system files and so forth.

00:41:22.245 --> 00:41:24.848
And we turned on all the
switches for optimized storage.

00:41:24.848 --> 00:41:29.686
And we went from 20 gigs
free to 150 gigs free.

00:41:29.686 --> 00:41:30.654 line:92%
So, we think that's going

00:41:30.654 --> 00:41:32.522
to make a difference
for all of you.

00:41:32.522 --> 00:41:36.693 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:41:36.693 --> 00:41:40.063 line:92%
Next, Apple Pay.

00:41:40.063 --> 00:41:45.235
So, we all love using Apple Pay
in stores to pay with our phones

00:41:45.235 --> 00:41:48.071
and our Apple Watch
at the cash register

00:41:48.071 --> 00:41:51.675
and to shop inside apps
on our iOS devices.

00:41:51.675 --> 00:41:52.642 line:92%
So, of course, we wanted

00:41:52.642 --> 00:41:55.679
to bring this experience
to the Mac.

00:41:55.679 --> 00:41:59.115
We thought long and hard about
exactly the right way to do it.

00:41:59.115 --> 00:42:01.384 line:92%
And I think we'd nailed it.

00:42:02.485 --> 00:42:08.992 line:92%
[ Laughter and Applause ]

00:42:08.992 --> 00:42:10.994
I think we might have
an accessory business

00:42:10.994 --> 00:42:13.129
for some carrying straps,
can be very helpful.

00:42:13.129 --> 00:42:15.198
No, this is not how people
are going to shop on our Macs.

00:42:15.198 --> 00:42:17.801
We shop online, on
the web, in Safari.

00:42:17.801 --> 00:42:19.803 line:92%
And so, what are we doing?

00:42:19.803 --> 00:42:22.505
We're bringing Apple
Pay to the web.

00:42:22.505 --> 00:42:28.211 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:42:28.211 --> 00:42:31.581
So now, when you're shopping
online, you'll have a Pay

00:42:31.581 --> 00:42:33.950
with Apple Pay button
available to you.

00:42:33.950 --> 00:42:37.187
When you click it, a sheet comes
down that actually prompts you

00:42:37.187 --> 00:42:41.224
to securely authenticate your
purchase using continuity right

00:42:41.224 --> 00:42:43.526 line:92%
on your iPhone with Touch ID.

00:42:43.526 --> 00:42:49.566 line:92%
[ Applause ]

00:42:49.566 --> 00:42:53.003
And of course, this works
with your Apple Watch as well.

00:42:53.003 --> 00:42:56.072
So, you can authenticate with
just a tap on your wrist.

00:42:56.072 --> 00:42:58.174
And already, many, many
merchants are signed

00:42:58.174 --> 00:43:00.710
up to bring their
web storefronts

00:43:00.710 --> 00:43:02.245 line:92%
to support Apple Pay on the web.

00:43:02.245 --> 00:43:05.548
And Apple Pay is expanding
hugely geographically.

00:43:05.548 --> 00:43:09.653
It's now available in the
United States, the UK, Canada,

00:43:09.653 --> 00:43:12.322 line:92%
Australia, China and Singapore.

00:43:12.322 --> 00:43:13.723 line:92%
And in the next few months,

00:43:13.723 --> 00:43:17.661
it's coming to Switzerland,
France and Hong Kong.

00:43:17.661 --> 00:43:19.229
Now, next, I want
to move to part

00:43:19.229 --> 00:43:22.298
of the Mac experience,
and that's tabs.

00:43:22.298 --> 00:43:26.536
You know, many of us love using
tabs to take a mess of windows

00:43:26.536 --> 00:43:29.305
that we have in Safari and
get them neatly organized

00:43:29.305 --> 00:43:30.674 line:92%
in tab set.

